hing.module.ts` - 引入 `ImModule`". But the actual file doesn\'t show `ImModule`
being imported. However, the `@OnEvent` decorator from `@nestjs/event-emitter` d
oesn\'t require module import - it works globally through the `EventEmitterModul
e`. So this is actually fine.\n\n5. Looking at `im.service.ts` line 412-424, the
`getConversations` method uses native SQL with `?` placeholders - that\'s correc
t per the spec.\n\n6. But wait - there\'s a potential issue in `im.service.ts` `
