t all\n   - Migration 已提交 — not checked\n   - 实时通信契约已同步 — not checke
d\n   - 原生 SQL 占位符合规 — not checked\n   \n   The developer checked "代码、
测试、文档三同步" but didn\'t actually run `make test`. This is contradictory.\n
\n2. **SwChatInputBar 缺少 Maestro 自动全选逻辑** - Per `docs/design-docs/flutte
r.md` lines 636-648, TextFields must auto-select all text on focus to prevent Ma
estro `inputText` from appending. The `SwChatInputBar` component doesn\'t implem
ent this.\n\n3. **SendMessageDto.content 可选性与服务层校验语义不一致** - The DT
O marks `content` as `@IsOptional()` but the custom validator `IsMessageContent(
)` is only run when content is present. Missing content for text messages passes
DTO validation but then hits Service layer `BusinessException`. Per `docs/design
-docs/nestjs.md` lines 140-171, DTO validation strategy and Service defense logi
c must be semantically consistent.\n\nWait, should #3 be Blocking or Major? It\'
s a semantic inconsistency that causes validation to happen at the wrong layer, 
but it doesn\'t break functionality. I\'ll classify it as Major.\n\nActually, le
t me reconsider issue #2. Is it Blocking? The spec says Maestro E2E is mandatory
. If the input field doesn\'t auto-select, Maestro tests that input text will fa
il or produce wrong results. This is a real functional issue for E2E. I\'ll mark
it as Major, not Blocking, because the component still works for human users.\n\
nLet me finalize my Blocking issues:\n1. **模板检查清单未完整执行** - This is th
e strongest Blocking issue because it means critical verification steps were ski
pped.\n\nDo I have any other Blocking issues?\n\nLet me think about the `sequenc
e_id: 0` issue again. In `message.entity.ts`:\n```typescript\n@Column("bigint")\
n@Generated("increment")\nsequence_id: number;\n```\n\nAnd in the service:\n```t
ypescript\nsequence_id: 0, // Will be replaced by auto-increment\n```\n\nTypeORM
\'s `@Generated("increment")` on a non-primary column is problematic. Looking at
TypeORM source code and documentation, `@Generated("increment")` is typically us
ed for primary generated columns or UUID columns. For non-primary auto-increment
in MySQL, TypeORM behavior is not well-defined.\n\nActually, looking at TypeORM 
tests and issues, `@Generated("increment")` should work for non-primary columns 
in MySQL. When `save()` is called, TypeORM will include the column in the INSERT
with the provided value (0). MySQL will then auto-increment it (treating 0 as "n
ext value" by default). But this depends on the SQL mode.\n\nHowever, there\'s a
bigger issue: the migration defines `sequence_id BIGINT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT`
. In MySQL, only ONE column per table can be AUTO_INCREMENT, and it must be inde
xed. The migration creates an index on `sequence_id`, so that\'s fine. But wait 
- the `id` column is the primary key (CHAR(36)), so `sequence_id` is a separate 
auto-increment column. MySQL supports this as long as there\'s an index on the a
uto-increment column.\n\nActually, looking at the migration more carefully:\n```
sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS messages (\n  id CHAR(36) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,\
n  ...\n  sequence_id BIGINT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,\n  ...\n  INDEX idx_messag
es_sequence_id (sequence_id),\n  ...\n);\n```\n\nThis is valid in MySQL. The `se
quence_id` is auto-increment and indexed.\n\nBut the question is: does TypeORM p
roperly handle `@Generated("increment")` on this column? When you call `repo.cre
ate({ sequence_id: 0 })` and then `repo.save()`, TypeORM might include `sequence
_id = 0` in the INSERT. MySQL\'s default behavior for auto-increment columns is:
\n- If you insert 0, it generates the next auto-increment value (unless `NO_AUTO
_VALUE_ON_ZERO` SQL mode is enabled)\n- If you insert NULL, it generates the nex
t auto-increment value\n\nBut TypeORM with `@Generated("increment")` should idea
lly omit the column from the INSERT if the value is undefined/null, and then rel
oad it after insert. By explicitly setting `sequence_id: 0`, the code is relying
on MySQL\'s special handling of 0 for auto-increment columns.\n\nIs this a Block
ing issue? Probably not, since MySQL\'s default behavior handles it. But it\'s f
ragile.\n\nLet me check one more thing: does the test mock properly handle this?
In `im.service.spec.ts`:\n```typescript\nmessageRepo.create.mockReturnValue({\n 
...\n  sequence_id: 0,\n  ...\n});\nmessageRepo.save.mockResolvedValue({\n  ...\
n  sequence_id: 1,\n  ...\n});\n```\n\nThe mock returns `sequence_id: 1` after s
ave, so the tests pass. But this doesn\'t verify the actual database behavior.\n
\nI think the `sequence_id: 0` issue is a Minor concern at best, not Blocking.\n
\n**Major Issues:**\n\n1. **SwChatInputBar 缺少焦点自动全选，违反 Maestro E2E 规
范** - Per `docs/design-docs/flutter.md` lines 636-648, TextFields must auto-sel
ect on focus for Maestro compatibility.\n\n2. **SendMessageDto.content 可选性与
业务语义不一致** - `@IsOptional()` on `content` means missing content passes DTO
validation, but Service layer throws. Per NestJS spec, DTO should enforce requir
ed fields. This causes wrong HTTP status (Service returns 400, but it should be 
DTO validation 400 - same status, but wrong layer) and dead code in the Service 
for length validation (which IS dead code because DTO already validates length).
\n\nWait, is the Service length check dead code? The DTO\'s `IsMessageContent` v
alidates `type === "text" && value.length > 500` returns false. So yes, DTO reje
cts >500 char text messages. But the Service also checks `dto.content.length > 5
00`. This is dead code because DTO already rejects it. The only reachable part i
s `!dto.content`.\n\nPer NestJS spec:\n> 如果 DTO 中将字段标记为必填（如 `@IsStr
ing()` 未加 `@IsOptional()`），则 `ValidationPipe` 会在请求到达 Controller 之前
拦截缺失字段，返回 400 错误。此时 Service 层写的 `?? fallback` 防御逻辑是**永远
不会执行的死代码**。\n\nIn this case, the DTO doesn\'t mark content as required,
so the Service check `!dto.content` IS reachable. But the length check IS dead c
ode. This is a semantic inconsistency.\n\n3. **缺少独立的 Design-Only PR** - Per
`docs/design-docs/flutter.md` lines 377-419, new UI components should go through
a Design-Only PR first. This PR directly writes to `packages/design-system/`.\n\
n4. **`make test` / `make lint` 未执行且未提供替代证据** - Actually, I already h
ave this as Blocking. Let me not double-count.\n\nLet me reconsider the classifi
cation. The template checklist issue is Blocking. The other issues are Major or 
Minor.\n\n**Minor Issues:**\n- PR description inaccuracy about `matching.module.
ts` importing `ImModule`\n- BDD push notification test is a TODO stub\n- `im.gat
eway.ts` doesn\'t retroactively emit `message:delivered` when offline user comes
online\n\nWait, I should also check if there\'s an issue with the `conversation_
list_page.dart` using `context.push(\'/chat\', extra: {...})`. This is fine with
go_router.\n\nLet me also check one more thing: In `im.gateway.ts`, `handleSendM
essage` emits `message:receive` to the receiver room, but what about the sender?
Should the sender also receive their own message via Socket? Looking at the impl
ementation, the sender gets `message:ack` and `message:delivered`, but not `mess
age:receive`. The Mobile app handles the sent message optimistically in the BLoC
. This seems correct.\n\nWait, but what if the sender sends a message from anoth
er device? They wouldn\'t see it on this device unless they pull via HTTP. But t
hat\'s an edge case for MVP.\n\nLet me also verify the `markAsRead` HTTP endpoin
t vs Socket event. The Mobile uses Socket `message:read` for real-time mark-as-r
ead. The HTTP `POST /messages/read` endpoint also exists. Both use the same Serv
ice method. This is fine.\n\nLet me check one more potential issue: In `im.servi
ce.ts` `getConversations`, the query uses `new Date(cursor)` for the cursor. If 
