hich when passed to TypeORM/MySQL could cause issues. The DTO only validates tha
t `cursor` is a string (`@IsString()`). It doesn\'t validate it\'s a valid ISO d
ate string. This is a potential issue but not critical.\n\nActually, looking at 
`GetConversationsQueryDto`:\n```typescript\n@IsOptional()\n@IsString()\ncursor?:
string;\n```\n\nAnd in the service:\n```typescript\nif (cursor) {\n  participant
Qb.andWhere("c.updated_at < :cursor", {\n    cursor: new Date(cursor),\n  });\n}
\n```\n\nIf `cursor` is not a valid date, `new Date(cursor)` returns `Invalid Da
te`. TypeORM might convert this to `NULL` or some invalid value in the SQL query
